Job Description:
To be a part of the company?s Mutual Fund research initiative. This would involve:
Review and analyse Mutual Funds from a fundamental, qualitative perspective;
Develop opinion on Mutual Funds based on research not limited to risk and returns alone;
Source and analyse data related to Mutual Funds from the company?s internal databases, external databases as well as through secondary research;
Periodically meet fund managers and other key personnel in asset management companies either individually or as part of a team to assess qualitative factors that affect fund performance;
Monitor important developments in the mutual fund industry, regulatory framework, capital markets and the broader economy
Efficiently organise research to form independent, long-term and investor-centric investment hypothesis;
Participate in review meetings with the company?s internal teams to debate, discuss, and justify the investment hypothesis;
Prepare comprehensive, unbiased, succinct research reports;
Contribute towards enhancing and augmenting the company?s research methodology over time;
Execute any other assignments that may be undertaken by the Research team from time to time
Location
Mumbai
Key Skills
The candidate must:
Have in-depth knowledge of Indian Mutual Funds and other asset classes;
Understand both Debt and Equity markets;
Be aware of regulations governing mutual funds.
Be able to identify investment strategies;
Have excellent business writing skills;
Have excellent command over MS Excel;
Have excellent communication skills;
Be self-motivated and be able to work independently;
Familiarity with ICRA Online?s ?MFI explorer? product is desirable
Experience
Relevant experience in Mutual Fund research of 2 to 4 years
Education
MBA (Finance), CA, CFA
Information Security responsibility
Maintain Confidentiality and Integrity of organization information;
Identify and report security breaches
